Where else could we go?

275
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:24,680
[whimpering]
We are lucky

276
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:27,720
to be servants

277
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:31,680
in the house of kind masters.

278
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:33,120
[sniffles]

279
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:36,920
Lord Hora is like an angel to us.

280
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:41,720
Are you saying that
Lady Champa is a devil?

281
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:44,800
Did I say that, Chik?

282
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:46,840
Not directly.

283
00:21:48,360 --> 00:21:50,680
At the market, people are saying that

284
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:55,440
King Narai is sick.

285
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:56,880
We say "in poor health."

286
00:21:57,880 --> 00:22:00,400
Boong, use the right term.

287
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,800
How is it different?

288
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:06,560
I'm going to see Lady Champa.

289
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:08,560
You're not upset at her
anymore, aren't you?

290
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:12,400
[dramatic music]

291
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:17,520
I'm not upset.

292
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:21,440
She suspected me

293
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:23,720
because I was the only one

294
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:26,840
who could go in and out of her bedroom.

295
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:29,280
[Prik] That's why she accused me.

296
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:32,840
If she hadn't

297
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:36,120
but thought of me as a thief,

298
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:39,520
how could we still live
under the same roof?

299
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:41,960
[sniffling]

300
00:22:42,560 --> 00:22:43,920
We live in their house.

301
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:46,840
We eat from the same pot.

302
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:51,640
It's not that big of a deal to be accused
of stealing for just a few days.

303
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:54,440
Yes.

304
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,880
[whimpers]

305
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:01,080
King Narai is in poor health.

306
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:03,600
[ominous music]

307
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,080
[Choi] They say he's gravely ill.

308
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:07,360
Oh, no.

309
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:14,240
[Shorty chanting] <i><font color="white">"You can behold
my hollow,</font></i>

310
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:22,320
<i><font color="white">Sunken cheeks</font></i>

311
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:29,680
<i><font color="white">With bite marks underneath,</font></i>

312
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:36,040
<i><font color="white">Like an arrow piercing through my heart</font></i>

313
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:41,040
<i><font color="white">Enraptured by the thought of
Your tender lips,</font></i>

314
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:47,480
<i><font color="white">I writhe like a snake in sorrow</font></i>

315
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:50,240
[ominous music]

316
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:06,560
[Shorty chanting] <i><font color="white">The raging torment
of love scourges me,</font></i>

317
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:13,880
<i><font color="white">And may I be consumed
By either sorrow or death</font></i>

318
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:20,960
<i><font color="white">I can still smell</font></i>

319
00:24:21,520 --> 00:24:27,560
<i><font color="white">Your scented cheeks</font></i>

320
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:35,080
<i><font color="white">Though I've got two empty arms,
Without you to hold indeed,</font></i>

321
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:42,040
<i><font color="white">My love for you is still buried deep</font></i>

322
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:45,400
[sniffles]

323
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:47,960
[somber music]

324
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:49,920
[in sluggish voice]
Shorty.

325
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:57,600
My son.

326
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:05,400
[breathing heavily]
It hurts.

327
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:11,120
I can't...

328
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:16,640
protect you.

329
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:19,320
[dramatic music]

330
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:21,800
[sobbing]

331
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:28,120
Take care of yourself.

332
00:25:29,120 --> 00:25:31,200
[sobbing]

333
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:35,280
[dramatic music]

334
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:06,600
[Phaulkon] Prince Pi.

335
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:15,440
Are you ready to be the king?

336
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:17,640
[tense music]

337
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:20,480
Then I'll carry out the plan.

338
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:24,360
Wouldn't the people reject me?

339
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:26,040
Why?

340
00:26:27,040 --> 00:26:28,680
I'm not an heir to the throne

341
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:31,320
like Prince Apaiyatot and Prince Noi.

342
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:34,720
Everyone knows how you are
related to King Narai.

343
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:43,200
That I'm his son?

344
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:47,480
I don't have any right
to claim the throne.

345
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:53,320
Both of his brothers deserve it

346
00:26:54,120 --> 00:26:55,400
more than I do.

347
00:26:57,080 --> 00:26:59,080
[percussive music]

348
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:17,600
There will be a big change.

349
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:19,600
What is it?

350
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:23,440
Anyhow,

351
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:28,080
what are Earl Phetracha and Count Sorasak

352
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:31,160
doing at the moment?

353
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:35,040
[tense music]

354
00:27:41,720 --> 00:27:44,280
[Phetracha] They forced monks to leave
the monkhood and do slave labor.

355
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:47,000
That's demeaning.

356
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:50,600
But what we should be worried about
are their armed soldiers

357
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:53,680
who have been stationed
at the Bangkok fortress.

358
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:56,240
General Desfarges is in charge of them.

359
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:57,440
[Sorasak] And...

360
00:27:58,520 --> 00:28:00,840
they can open fire on us
anytime they want.

361
00:28:01,760 --> 00:28:03,560
[Phetracha] King Narai is seriously
in poor health.

362
00:28:04,800 --> 00:28:06,640
He doesn't allow anyone to see him,

363
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:08,760
except for that foreigner

364
00:28:09,360 --> 00:28:10,680
and that limping Shorty.

365
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:15,280
[monk 1] The word "Thai" means freedom.

366
00:28:16,080 --> 00:28:18,360
Ayutthaya is a Buddhist nation.

367
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:22,040
And it cannot be...

368
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:23,920
defeated.

369
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:26,840
[uplifting music]

370
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:47,080
[Champa sobbing]

371
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:49,720
[tranquil music]

372
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:53,080
[sobbing]

373
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:01,360
Si.
[sobs]

374
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:03,280
My son.

375
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:05,480
Why do you have to hurry back?

376
00:29:06,080 --> 00:29:09,080
Can't you stay with me
for a few more months?

377
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:12,040
If I stay here that long,

378
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:15,160
Marquess Ram will find out.

379
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:18,160
[whimpers]

380
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:23,080
He would claim the punishment
that was handed down by the King

381
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:25,880
and accuse me again.

382
00:29:27,240 --> 00:29:28,920
[Si] I'm blessed enough

383
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:32,240
that I could sneak into the capital

384
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:38,280
to pay my last respects to Father
for the last time.

385
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:41,440
[sobbing]

386
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:44,080
How much longer

387
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:49,120
will you finish serving your punishment?

388
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:52,160
It won't be long.

389
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:53,840
At present,

390
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:56,920
I've been good in Nakhon Si Thammarat,

391
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:01,480
and my lord there is quite fond of me.

392
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:09,640
But you still need to be careful.

393
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:16,160
Wasn't it because King Narai
was very fond of you

394
00:30:18,360 --> 00:30:20,520
that others in the palace

395
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:22,920
came to dislike you

396
00:30:24,440 --> 00:30:25,920
and tell on you?

397
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:29,520
That was the reason you were banished
and had to go live in Nakhon Si Thammarat.

398
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:33,080
[somber music]

399
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:36,520
Bear this in mind.

400
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:39,560
You can be good

401
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:41,840
but don't be outstanding.

402
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:44,480
It will get you into trouble.

403
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:55,720
[dramatic music]

404
00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:08,640
It won't be long

405
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:13,040
until I come back to take care of you.

406
00:31:15,320 --> 00:31:18,520
I'll come back
to serve King Narai, my lord,

407
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:22,040
in return for his kindness.

408
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:28,200
If one day,

409
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:31,400
he finds out the truth

410
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,640
that I didn't do anything wrong,

411
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:42,200
karma will punish those who wronged me.

412
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:44,680
[tense music]

413
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:47,480
[sobbing]

414
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,080
My son.

415
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:53,480
[sobbing]

416
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:57,320
[tense music]

417
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:19,640
-[Si] Choi.
-Yes, my lord.

418
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:21,960
What's wrong?

419
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:27,120
[dramatic music]

420
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,640
My father is dead.

421
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,560
The house seems so empty and gloomy.

422
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:41,960
Take good care of my mother,

423
00:32:43,560 --> 00:32:44,800
my brother, Dech,

424
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:50,400
and my sister-in-law, Karaked.

425
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,720
[tranquil music]

426
00:32:56,440 --> 00:32:57,520
I'm leaving.

427
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:01,360
[dramatic music]

428
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:03,440
Where are you...

429
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:21,560
Have a safe journey.

430
00:33:27,680 --> 00:33:29,680
[tranquil music]

431
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:38,960
[light music]

432
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:06,560
Do you still feel dizzy?

433
00:34:08,520 --> 00:34:09,640
Not anymore.

434
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:12,080
But I just feel

435
00:34:12,960 --> 00:34:14,760
a little bit plump.

436
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:18,280
What do you mean by "plump?"

437
00:34:19,560 --> 00:34:20,840
You're pregnant.

438
00:34:21,360 --> 00:34:23,200
You look plump in a healthy way.

439
00:34:29,400 --> 00:34:30,680
Even if...

440
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:33,840
you get as fat as a pig,

441
00:34:35,080 --> 00:34:36,440
you will still be my wife.

442
00:34:37,720 --> 00:34:40,720
Really, as fat as a pig?

443
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:42,640
[soft chuckle]

444
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:50,080
It's what's on the inside

445
00:34:50,680 --> 00:34:52,040
that I've fallen in love with.

446
00:34:52,680 --> 00:34:54,120
Not your appearance.

447
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:58,680
Otherwise,

448
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:01,080
I would have loved you

449
00:35:03,080 --> 00:35:04,920
when you were the old Karaked.

450
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:07,320
[romantic music]

451
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:13,880
Even if you get ugly

452
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:17,880
or get so fat that I can't
put my arms around you,

453
00:35:20,760 --> 00:35:22,240
for me,

454
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:25,960
you will still be my one and only Karaked.

455
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:34,800
[romantic music]

456
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:48,440
[romantic music continues]

457
00:35:54,640 --> 00:35:55,920
<i><font color="white">Khun Pi.</font></i>

458
00:35:56,880 --> 00:35:58,920
Is it true that King Narai
is in poor health?

459
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:02,560
Yes.

460
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:04,080
He's gravely ill.

461
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:07,680
He doesn't allow anyone to see him,

462
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:10,160
except for Prince Pi

463
00:36:10,920 --> 00:36:12,200
and Duke Wichayen.

464
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:14,640
Really?

465
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:17,280
[ominous music]

466
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:24,680
[Ketsurang] <i><font color="white">After all, Prince Pi,</font></i>

467
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:26,440
<i><font color="white">Prince Noi,</font></i>

468
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:28,520
<i><font color="white">and Prince Apaiyatot</font></i>

469
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:31,520
<i><font color="white">will be killed by Earl Phetracha.</font></i>

470
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:34,680
[ominous music]

471
00:36:39,080 --> 00:36:42,920
[Ketsurang] <i><font color="white">The only one who can stop
Duke Wichayen</font></i>

472
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:45,200
<i><font color="white">is Earl Phetracha.</font></i>

473
00:36:48,240 --> 00:36:50,680
<i><font color="white">Everything is happening
according to history.</font></i>

474
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:52,360
<i><font color="white">Ketsurang,</font></i>

475
00:36:52,480 --> 00:36:54,600
<i><font color="white">stop thinking about it.</font></i>

476
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:58,160
<i><font color="white">You didn't come back here
to change history.</font></i>

477
00:36:58,720 --> 00:37:00,240
<i><font color="white">You came back here to meet</font></i> Khun Pi.

478
00:37:01,160 --> 00:37:03,880
<i><font color="white">You came back here
because of the destiny of love.</font></i>

479
00:37:06,440 --> 00:37:08,040
Even if you want to do something about it,

480
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:11,240
do you think it would change anything?

481
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:14,160
[action music]

482
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:15,560
[elephant trumpets]

483
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:19,360
-[men shouting]
-[swords clanging]

484
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,960
[action music]

485
00:37:28,360 --> 00:37:34,680
-[men shouting]
-[swords clanging]

486
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:39,760
[Sorasak] Duke Wichayen

487
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:42,080
is definitely behind that limping Shorty.

488
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:45,280
We are still not sure
whether King Narai agrees with this.

489
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:47,880
I think it's possible.

490
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:51,920
He never cares about his brothers,

491
00:37:53,520 --> 00:37:55,440
even though they have
the right to claim the throne.

492
00:37:55,960 --> 00:37:56,880
Both of them.

493
00:37:57,160 --> 00:37:59,160
[ominous music]

494
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:00,800
[Phetracha] The city will be in turmoil

495
00:38:01,160 --> 00:38:03,680
just because of a lowly foreign bastard.

496
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:05,960
The King trusts him.

497
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:08,720
He has put so much faith in him,

498
00:38:09,200 --> 00:38:10,280
that Duke Wichayen.

499
00:38:10,680 --> 00:38:12,680
[ominous music]

500
00:38:14,360 --> 00:38:16,040
So what are you going to do?

501
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:18,480
[elephant roars]

502
00:38:19,680 --> 00:38:21,680
[ominous music]

503
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:28,760
My son...

504
00:38:31,560 --> 00:38:33,400
if I'm going to do something

505
00:38:34,520 --> 00:38:36,920
that you think I should do,

506
00:38:40,440 --> 00:38:41,800
I want you to know that

507
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:46,160
it's not because I want to be in power...

508
00:38:51,840 --> 00:38:53,360
But because there's a situation

509
00:38:54,920 --> 00:38:57,240
that will bring disaster to our country.

510
00:38:58,120 --> 00:39:00,120
[action music]

511
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:16,480
-[roosters crowing]
-[men shouting]

512
00:39:18,680 --> 00:39:20,280
[men shouting]

513
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:22,360
[tense music]

514
00:39:26,200 --> 00:39:28,200
-[roosters crowing]
-[men shouting]

515
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:30,480
[tense music]

516
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:32,360
[Phaulkon] Men.

517
00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:34,480
Get them out of the way. I'm in a hurry.

518
00:39:34,960 --> 00:39:35,840
[servant 1] Hey.

519
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:38,240
Get out of the way.
The foreign master is passing through.

520
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:39,720
[servant 1] Now.

521
00:39:40,200 --> 00:39:42,200
[tense music]

522
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:44,760
[grunts]

523
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:45,960
-[thwacks]
-[groans]

524
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:47,280
[gasps]

525
00:39:47,560 --> 00:39:49,720
[crowd murmuring]

526
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:52,240
Bring me the one who did this!

527
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:54,400
[tense music]

528
00:39:54,920 --> 00:39:56,160
Hey, get off me!

529
00:39:57,040 --> 00:39:58,360
Selling yourselves to that foreigner!

530
00:39:58,720 --> 00:40:00,840
[man 1] Get off me!

531
00:40:01,040 --> 00:40:02,640
-[thuds]
-[grunts]

532
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,320
How dare you.

533
00:40:08,840 --> 00:40:09,800
Punish him.

534
00:40:10,200 --> 00:40:11,680
-[thumping]
-[grunting]

535
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:14,360
-[screams]
-[thumping]

536
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:17,600
Stop! Go away!

537
00:40:17,680 --> 00:40:21,560
Stop abusing us! Go! Go away!

538
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:24,240
Choi, what are you standing there for?
Come here!

539
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:25,600
Chuang, help me.

540
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:27,320
-Prik.
-Why do we have to be afraid?

541
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:28,840
-They are just foreigners.
-[Choi] Prik.

542
00:40:29,080 --> 00:40:31,960
Why? Why are you scared of them?
[groans]

543
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:32,920
Prik.

544
00:40:33,040 --> 00:40:35,160
-What?
-Do you want to die?

545
00:40:35,240 --> 00:40:36,720
-[scoffs]
-He's right.

546
00:40:36,840 --> 00:40:38,880
Prik, look at his eyes.

547
00:40:38,960 --> 00:40:40,080
[Chuang] He looks really angry.

548
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:42,000
I'll take responsibility
for whatever happens.

549
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:43,000
-[Prik] Go.
-[Choi] Hey.

550
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:45,080
[quirky music]

551
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:47,560
-Hey! Don't come any closer!
-Don't!

552
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:48,680
Stop!

553
00:40:48,760 --> 00:40:50,560
-[Prik] Go!
-[Phaulkon] I said stop!

554
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:52,480
Take the one who threw it

555
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:55,400
to flog him 20 times.

556
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:57,480
Then, throw him in jail.

557
00:40:57,560 --> 00:40:59,560
[tense music]

558
00:40:59,640 --> 00:41:01,840
Don't do that to him! How could you?

559
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:02,960
Stop it, you hag!

560
00:41:03,440 --> 00:41:05,440
[tense music]

561
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:07,600
Even I'm a hag, what's it to you?

562
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:10,120
Who is this old hag?

563
00:41:10,240 --> 00:41:12,040
I'm a citizen of Ayutthaya.

564
00:41:12,400 --> 00:41:13,360
[scoffs]

565
00:41:17,440 --> 00:41:18,960
He's staring at me.

566
00:41:19,920 --> 00:41:21,120
You will die soon.

567
00:41:21,320 --> 00:41:23,440
-What?
-[Choi] Prik.

568
00:41:23,560 --> 00:41:24,720
-[Prik] Let me go.
-[Choi] Prik.

569
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:25,840
[Chuang] Prik.

570
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:29,200
[tense music]

571
00:41:38,360 --> 00:41:39,440
[Prik sighs]

572
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:41,240
Give me that, Prik.

573
00:41:41,320 --> 00:41:42,520
Well,

574
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:45,600
I really wanted to climb up the litter.

575
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:47,320
[Choi] Really?
And what would you do to him?

576
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:48,480
[Prik] Hey, Choi.

577
00:41:48,560 --> 00:41:49,880
I was going to kick him.

578
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:53,200
Good. And you would get beheaded for that.

579
00:41:53,320 --> 00:41:54,880
-[all chuckling]
-Well, well.

580
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:58,000
-Or you might end up being at the temple.
-Why, Chik?

581
00:41:58,160 --> 00:42:00,400
Well, to have the monks chant
for you since you would be dead.

582
00:42:00,520 --> 00:42:03,120
-[all chuckling]
-You brat! You're so rude.

583
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:04,920
Prik.

584
00:42:05,040 --> 00:42:06,320
Does he even realize

585
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:08,920
that people hate him and his men so much?

586
00:42:09,160 --> 00:42:11,800
-He will get beaten up one day.
-Oh.

587
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:14,720
[Prik] And listen to me carefully.
I will be one of those...

588
00:42:17,320 --> 00:42:19,160
who will kick his butt.

589
00:42:19,520 --> 00:42:20,360
[grunts]

590
00:42:20,960 --> 00:42:22,960
[ominous music]

591
00:42:34,520 --> 00:42:36,000
[Lord Rueang] King Narai is
in poor health.

592
00:42:36,160 --> 00:42:37,440
He cannot perform his duties.

593
00:42:39,560 --> 00:42:41,760
Duke Wichayen has been gaining
more and more power every day

594
00:42:42,120 --> 00:42:44,520
since he was promoted to
Chancellor of Interior

595
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:46,800
and became in charge of all civil affairs.

596
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:48,440
Our people...

597
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:50,720
are being badly oppressed.

598
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:53,200
[tense music]

599
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:56,120
Karaked.

600
00:42:58,520 --> 00:42:59,360
Yes?

601
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:01,920
Can you tell us now?

602
00:43:02,040 --> 00:43:04,120
What did you hear

603
00:43:04,320 --> 00:43:08,520
when you spied on Phaulkon and Desfarges?

604
00:43:08,920 --> 00:43:10,920
[tense music]

605
00:43:17,040 --> 00:43:19,080
Yes, I'll tell you now.

606
00:43:22,240 --> 00:43:24,280
I heard them talking about soldiers.

607
00:43:25,920 --> 00:43:29,320
General Desfarges is going
to bring French soldiers here

608
00:43:29,880 --> 00:43:33,600
when Duke Wichayen sends
a messenger to him.

609
00:43:34,040 --> 00:43:36,040
[tense music]

610
00:43:38,080 --> 00:43:39,600
They must have planned something vicious.

611
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:42,240
Don't you think so, Dech?

612
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:45,920
Listen to Karaked first.

613
00:43:46,720 --> 00:43:48,600
I'm sure she has more to say.

614
00:43:50,760 --> 00:43:52,760
[ominous music]

615
00:43:54,120 --> 00:43:55,720
Duke Wichayen said that

616
00:43:55,960 --> 00:43:57,520
the King's health is in a critical state.

617
00:43:59,680 --> 00:44:00,920
And their scheme

618
00:44:02,160 --> 00:44:03,480
will be carried out soon.

619
00:44:04,840 --> 00:44:06,280
[both] A rebellion?

620
00:44:07,200 --> 00:44:09,200
[tense music]

621
00:44:10,760 --> 00:44:13,400
I heard that a group of people
have been planning for an uprising.

622
00:44:14,160 --> 00:44:15,600
Who are those people?

623
00:44:17,640 --> 00:44:19,120
His brothers, Prince Noi

624
00:44:19,600 --> 00:44:20,880
and Prince Apaiyatot.

625
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:24,240
[Lord Rueang] They have
gathered so many people.

626
00:44:24,800 --> 00:44:26,680
We don't know when
they're going to stage a rebellion.

627
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:31,040
Also, Duke Wichayen
is supporting Prince Pi.

628
00:44:32,360 --> 00:44:34,440
He could eventually convince
the prince to total conversion.

629
00:44:34,520 --> 00:44:37,440
Where would Prince Pi
get military forces to stage a rebellion?

630
00:44:38,520 --> 00:44:39,560
He needs a force.

631
00:44:39,880 --> 00:44:41,480
He has his men in Phitsanulok.

632
00:44:44,680 --> 00:44:46,240
What about Earl Phetracha?

633
00:44:49,560 --> 00:44:51,560
[tense music]

634
00:44:57,320 --> 00:44:59,320
[tense music continues]

635
00:45:07,320 --> 00:45:08,880
I think it's time.

636
00:45:13,400 --> 00:45:14,920
[woman 1] King Narai hasn't recovered yet.

637
00:45:16,120 --> 00:45:18,400
That's why it's the right time to act.

638
00:45:22,040 --> 00:45:23,680
That foreigner is supporting Prince Pi.

639
00:45:27,120 --> 00:45:29,600
We have to get rid of Prince Pi
so that he won't have a puppet.

640
00:45:30,760 --> 00:45:32,040
Because in fact,

641
00:45:33,040 --> 00:45:34,760
Duke Wichayen is the one
who wants the throne.

642
00:45:38,560 --> 00:45:40,800
[woman 2] Prince Pi has never shown up
in front of people.

643
00:45:41,480 --> 00:45:42,840
How are we going to kill him?

644
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:46,080
We need to use someone close to him

645
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:48,560
or someone he respects to lure him out.

646
00:45:50,120 --> 00:45:52,120
[action music]

647
00:45:55,520 --> 00:45:57,600
I have been opposed to the King's idea

648
00:45:59,120 --> 00:46:01,520
of bringing the French soldiers
into our country.

649
00:46:03,520 --> 00:46:06,360
At the moment, the French
have control over our people.

650
00:46:07,920 --> 00:46:09,520
They belittle,

651
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:11,280
disdain,

652
00:46:11,720 --> 00:46:12,920
and patronize us.

653
00:46:14,320 --> 00:46:15,920
[Phetracha] I only have one purpose

654
00:46:16,520 --> 00:46:18,320
and one purpose alone,

655
00:46:23,800 --> 00:46:29,160
and that is to liberate Ayutthaya
from the French's influence.

656
00:46:30,000 --> 00:46:32,000
[action music]

657
00:46:44,120 --> 00:46:45,600
[Phetracha] Duke Kosathibodi,

658
00:46:49,600 --> 00:46:51,680
Prince Pi respects you.

659
00:46:52,960 --> 00:46:55,000
Even Prince Noi

660
00:46:55,880 --> 00:46:57,200
and Prince Apaiyatot

661
00:46:57,320 --> 00:47:00,960
have been good friends with you
since they were little.

662
00:47:02,080 --> 00:47:03,960
If you do not side with the French

663
00:47:04,560 --> 00:47:06,040
or with noblemen from other countries,

664
00:47:07,360 --> 00:47:09,640
please do as I ask.

665
00:47:10,360 --> 00:47:11,240
[sighs]

666
00:47:12,760 --> 00:47:15,320
I respect you as if
you are one of my relatives.

667
00:47:17,320 --> 00:47:21,080
You know, everyone in this kingdom
thinks that you are on my side.

668
00:47:23,160 --> 00:47:25,760
If someone else happens to be in power,

669
00:47:27,240 --> 00:47:29,960
I don't think they will let you
and your family go that easily.

670
00:47:30,240 --> 00:47:32,240
[tense music]

671
00:47:34,800 --> 00:47:36,320
This is difficult for me,

672
00:47:37,840 --> 00:47:39,240
because I know everyone involved.

673
00:47:40,040 --> 00:47:41,680
Even when it comes to Duke Wichayen,

674
00:47:42,640 --> 00:47:44,120
I still don't believe

675
00:47:45,560 --> 00:47:47,080
that he wants to overthrow King Narai.

676
00:47:47,920 --> 00:47:49,440
At this rate, you still don't believe it?

677
00:47:49,960 --> 00:47:51,960
[tense music]

678
00:48:05,520 --> 00:48:08,240
[drum thumping]

679
00:48:08,800 --> 00:48:15,000
[Shorty chanting] <i><font color="white">I can still smell</font></i>

680
00:48:15,840 --> 00:48:21,800
<i><font color="white">Your scented cheeks</font></i>

681
00:48:22,400 --> 00:48:28,320
<i><font color="white">Though I've got two empty arms,
Without you to hold indeed,</font></i>

682
00:48:29,200 --> 00:48:34,960
<i><font color="white">My love for you is still buried deep</font></i>

683
00:48:41,320 --> 00:48:43,320
[tranquil music]

684
00:48:57,160 --> 00:49:00,040
How dare the lord of Nakhon Si Thammarat

685
00:49:02,600 --> 00:49:06,040
execute one of my men

686
00:49:06,760 --> 00:49:08,760
without my permission.

687
00:49:10,760 --> 00:49:12,800
[whimpering]
Si has done

688
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:19,040
the same thing to me,

689
00:49:20,480 --> 00:49:22,840
but I didn't do such a thing to him.

690
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:28,520
I think I'll have to

691
00:49:31,040 --> 00:49:32,680
get rid of that lord.

692
00:49:34,240 --> 00:49:36,840
[coughing]

693
00:49:42,480 --> 00:49:45,240
[Narai coughing]

694
00:49:50,200 --> 00:49:52,240
[dramatic music]

695
00:50:08,200 --> 00:50:10,200
[ominous music]

696
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:22,320
Chancellor,

697
00:50:22,680 --> 00:50:24,200
I feel awful about this.

698
00:50:25,960 --> 00:50:27,640
I've told you so many times

699
00:50:28,600 --> 00:50:29,800
to trust me.

700
00:50:32,320 --> 00:50:33,840
I'm short and deformed.

701
00:50:34,200 --> 00:50:35,480
How could I be a king?

702
00:50:36,600 --> 00:50:38,160
[Shorty] I also don't have
any manpower here.

703
00:50:38,440 --> 00:50:40,320
The only manpower I have
is in Phitsanulok.

704
00:50:41,720 --> 00:50:42,560
I have.

705
00:50:43,280 --> 00:50:44,480
Your soldiers

706
00:50:44,600 --> 00:50:46,080
are in Bangkok, which is so far away.

707
00:50:46,800 --> 00:50:48,040
They will come here

708
00:50:48,640 --> 00:50:49,920
as soon as I call for them.

709
00:50:51,920 --> 00:50:53,880
Prince Apaiyatot, the King's brother,

710
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:57,320
insulted me, saying...

711
00:50:58,840 --> 00:50:59,960
"Shorty,

712
00:51:01,000 --> 00:51:02,520
don't even think about it.

713
00:51:04,240 --> 00:51:05,440
You have no right to it."

714
00:51:06,800 --> 00:51:09,160
He knows full well that you do.

715
00:51:10,960 --> 00:51:12,080
[Phaulkon] Prince Pi.

716
00:51:12,560 --> 00:51:15,840
Even King Narai would give you the throne,

717
00:51:18,040 --> 00:51:20,520
if he were conscious.

718
00:51:20,920 --> 00:51:22,920
[ominous music]

719
00:51:31,800 --> 00:51:33,080
I'm scared.

720
00:51:35,080 --> 00:51:36,160
Prince Pi.

721
00:51:37,440 --> 00:51:41,040
You are destined to be the new king.

722
00:51:43,120 --> 00:51:44,040
You can't deny it.

723
00:51:46,280 --> 00:51:48,280
[tense music]

724
00:52:02,640 --> 00:52:04,640
[light music]

725
00:52:11,680 --> 00:52:12,760
<i><font color="white">Khun Pi.</font></i>

726
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:16,960
Are you siding with the rebels,

727
00:52:17,200 --> 00:52:20,480
Earl Phetracha and Count Sorasak?

728
00:52:24,240 --> 00:52:25,160
[sighs deeply]

729
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:29,360
[exhales sharply]

730
00:52:29,440 --> 00:52:31,440
[light music]

731
00:52:33,160 --> 00:52:35,680
I don't know how
your people's lives had been

732
00:52:36,800 --> 00:52:37,920
before you came here.

733
00:52:38,720 --> 00:52:39,960
But here,

734
00:52:40,560 --> 00:52:43,360
we have to make sure that
we and our family survive,

735
00:52:44,720 --> 00:52:47,280
even if it means that
we have to get our hands dirty.

736
00:52:50,560 --> 00:52:52,520
The kingdom is in turmoil at the moment.

737
00:52:54,120 --> 00:52:55,280
I think

738
00:52:56,360 --> 00:52:59,840
Earl Phetracha will be
the one who can save it.

739
00:53:00,320 --> 00:53:02,160
[Dech] If we are talking about rights,

740
00:53:02,880 --> 00:53:05,080
Count Sorasak also has the right
as much as anyone else.

741
00:53:08,040 --> 00:53:09,080
Also,

742
00:53:10,520 --> 00:53:11,720
Prince Pi,

743
00:53:12,720 --> 00:53:14,360
though he has the right to the throne,

744
00:53:15,040 --> 00:53:16,400
he has already converted.

745
00:53:17,520 --> 00:53:19,120
He would only enhance
the outsiders' power.

746
00:53:19,800 --> 00:53:21,800
[tense music]

747
00:53:22,920 --> 00:53:24,080
I see.

748
00:53:24,560 --> 00:53:25,840
[Karaked] <i><font color="white">Khun Pi.</font></i>

749
00:53:27,600 --> 00:53:29,560
Does this mean Prince Noi,

750
00:53:29,680 --> 00:53:31,160
Prince Apaiyatot,

751
00:53:32,040 --> 00:53:33,920
and Prince Pi...

752
00:53:36,240 --> 00:53:38,080
will be killed?

753
00:53:38,280 --> 00:53:40,280
[ominous music]

754
00:53:40,920 --> 00:53:42,280
Karaked.

755
00:53:43,160 --> 00:53:44,600
Be honest with me.

756
00:53:45,480 --> 00:53:47,040
What do you know?

757
00:53:47,520 --> 00:53:49,520
[ominous music]

758
00:53:53,160 --> 00:53:55,560
I was just saying how it usually goes.

759
00:53:57,160 --> 00:54:00,160
Those men are their opponents.

760
00:54:00,760 --> 00:54:02,440
Why would Earl Phetracha

761
00:54:02,560 --> 00:54:05,480
keep them around
when they might attack him anytime?

762
00:54:06,040 --> 00:54:08,040
[tense music]

763
00:54:15,480 --> 00:54:17,160
It's history.

764
00:54:17,960 --> 00:54:19,520
History told me.

765
00:54:20,520 --> 00:54:21,760
[exhales sharply]

766
00:54:23,040 --> 00:54:25,080
What else do you know from it?

767
00:54:25,800 --> 00:54:29,080
Lord Pan still doesn't want
to take our sides.

768
00:54:30,080 --> 00:54:31,400
And if he doesn't,

769
00:54:31,640 --> 00:54:33,080
we can't get rid of Prince Pi

770
00:54:33,320 --> 00:54:35,320
and the other two princes.

771
00:54:36,680 --> 00:54:38,680
[tense music]

772
00:54:38,760 --> 00:54:40,200
He doesn't want to join us

773
00:54:41,280 --> 00:54:42,640
because he doesn't believe

774
00:54:44,280 --> 00:54:48,000
that Duke Wichayen
could betray King Narai.

775
00:54:49,800 --> 00:54:50,640
[exhales sharply]

776
00:54:50,720 --> 00:54:52,720
[tense music]

777
00:54:53,680 --> 00:54:55,640
Tell him

778
00:54:56,560 --> 00:54:57,840
that Duke Wichayen definitely could,

779
00:54:58,320 --> 00:54:59,680
as sure as eggs are eggs.

780
00:55:00,240 --> 00:55:02,360
You're saying odd things again.

781
00:55:03,080 --> 00:55:04,520
I don't want to hear something like that.

782
00:55:05,120 --> 00:55:06,560
Here's the thing.

783
00:55:08,960 --> 00:55:11,560
You go and tell Lord Pan

784
00:55:13,360 --> 00:55:14,960
that what Duke Wichayen is doing

785
00:55:16,040 --> 00:55:19,040
is something that will threaten
this kingdom.

786
00:55:21,080 --> 00:55:22,200
[Karaked] If we don't stop him,

787
00:55:22,640 --> 00:55:25,800
Ayutthaya would definitely
fall into chaos.

788
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:29,000
[tense music]

789
00:55:36,600 --> 00:55:39,120
What do you mean by "threat?"

790
00:55:40,960 --> 00:55:42,880
He will give this land to his master.

791
00:55:44,560 --> 00:55:46,840
To the King of his country, of course.
What else would it be?

792
00:55:46,920 --> 00:55:48,920
[tens music]

793
00:55:49,120 --> 00:55:50,320
That's right.

794
00:55:51,560 --> 00:55:53,160
We have proof.

795
00:55:54,480 --> 00:55:55,680
What proof?

796
00:55:56,160 --> 00:55:57,960
Someone secretly wrote a letter

797
00:55:58,200 --> 00:55:59,720
to a priest

798
00:56:00,880 --> 00:56:03,520
who is a royal mentor of Louis XIV.

799
00:56:04,160 --> 00:56:05,760
It was given to him discreetly.

800
00:56:07,600 --> 00:56:08,880
What did the letter say?

801
00:56:09,960 --> 00:56:10,840
It said

802
00:56:12,320 --> 00:56:13,880
that he would do anything

803
00:56:14,720 --> 00:56:17,360
for the benefit of the French companies.

804
00:56:18,680 --> 00:56:20,720
He will make Bangkok and Myeik

805
00:56:21,280 --> 00:56:22,920
fall under French influence.

806
00:56:23,840 --> 00:56:24,960
[Dech] It also said

807
00:56:25,400 --> 00:56:27,760
the King of this land is on his deathbed.

808
00:56:30,080 --> 00:56:32,640
He is looking for someone he can use
as a puppet to take over Siam.

809
00:56:34,600 --> 00:56:35,560
Wait.

810
00:56:36,280 --> 00:56:37,640
What did you say they will take over?

811
00:56:38,280 --> 00:56:39,400
Siam.

812
00:56:41,320 --> 00:56:43,360
That's what they call us.

813
00:56:44,360 --> 00:56:46,120
Why do they call us "Siam?"

814
00:56:46,240 --> 00:56:48,120
This land is called Ayutthaya.

815
00:56:48,880 --> 00:56:49,800
That's right.

816
00:56:50,560 --> 00:56:51,680
This is bizarre.

817
00:56:52,360 --> 00:56:53,440
Most importantly,

818
00:56:54,080 --> 00:56:55,760
the letter said that

819
00:56:56,480 --> 00:57:00,360
the King would have to grant him
the absolute power to rule this land,

820
00:57:01,320 --> 00:57:03,680
and that he would do everything
for the sake of France,

821
00:57:04,600 --> 00:57:06,160
including turning this land

822
00:57:07,120 --> 00:57:08,880
into a land of Christians.

823
00:57:09,240 --> 00:57:11,240
[tense music]

824
00:57:12,320 --> 00:57:13,760
I loathe them all.

825
00:57:14,960 --> 00:57:19,280
And I will drive all of them
out of Ayutthaya.

826
00:57:20,000 --> 00:57:22,000
[tense music]

827
00:57:25,000 --> 00:57:26,080
By the way, Dech,

828
00:57:26,440 --> 00:57:27,920
you said you have proof.

829
00:57:28,720 --> 00:57:29,960
[Lord Pan] What kind of proof?

830
00:57:30,920 --> 00:57:33,840
If that letter had been sent secretly,
how did you know about it? Hmm?

831
00:57:34,640 --> 00:57:35,880
Actually, Karaked did.

832
00:57:36,760 --> 00:57:38,760
[tense music]

833
00:57:48,320 --> 00:57:50,320
[tense music continues]

834
00:57:51,400 --> 00:57:52,960
[Karaked] The proof is that

835
00:57:54,800 --> 00:57:57,040
someone found the letter.

836
00:57:58,400 --> 00:58:00,360
I don't know how to prove it to you,

837
00:58:00,960 --> 00:58:02,440
but it's true.

838
00:58:03,840 --> 00:58:05,400
The letter is real,

839
00:58:06,160 --> 00:58:09,240
and it's in Duke Wichayen's handwriting.

840
00:58:10,840 --> 00:58:11,960
I believe you.

841
00:58:14,400 --> 00:58:16,840
I believe you the same way
Master believes you.

842
00:58:19,640 --> 00:58:21,080
I have no doubt about it.

843
00:58:22,760 --> 00:58:24,680
Are you sure about this, Lady Karaked?

844
00:58:25,360 --> 00:58:27,920
I'm sure about this more than anything.

845
00:58:30,160 --> 00:58:31,800
[Lord Pan] What about King Narai,
Lady Karaked?

846
00:58:32,040 --> 00:58:33,520
Does he know about their plans?

847
00:58:35,720 --> 00:58:37,720
There's no proof

848
00:58:38,200 --> 00:58:40,760
that King Narai agrees with Duke Wichayen,

849
00:58:41,000 --> 00:58:43,480
no matter how much the King favors him.

850
00:58:44,160 --> 00:58:46,160
I believe the King allowed him

851
00:58:48,040 --> 00:58:51,360
to bring 700 to 800 soldiers
into Ayutthaya.

852
00:58:54,880 --> 00:58:58,760
I believe he allowed them
to dock those ships and terrify us.

853
00:59:00,640 --> 00:59:02,480
[Phetracha] I feel terribly sorry for him,

854
00:59:03,280 --> 00:59:06,760
but I cannot let him
stay on the throne anymore.

855
00:59:08,320 --> 00:59:10,320
[action music]

856
00:59:11,320 --> 00:59:12,440
[Sorasak scoffs]

857
00:59:13,480 --> 00:59:14,680
Father,

858
00:59:16,280 --> 00:59:19,120
King Narai has been
in poor health for months.

859
00:59:21,600 --> 00:59:22,880
Why are you hesitating?

860
00:59:25,280 --> 00:59:26,240
[sighs]

861
00:59:27,480 --> 00:59:29,760
[Phetracha] Constance is getting
more and more impudent every day.

862
00:59:30,800 --> 00:59:36,120
Does he think that
nobody here can stop them?

863
00:59:39,840 --> 00:59:43,080
Do they think we are so stupid

864
00:59:45,080 --> 00:59:47,480
that we will let them
take over our land so easily?

865
00:59:51,120 --> 00:59:53,160
Not all of us are the same as King Narai.

866
00:59:56,400 --> 00:59:57,760
I must do this,

867
00:59:59,200 --> 01:00:00,920
even though I don't want to.

868
01:00:01,800 --> 01:00:03,800
[tense music]

869
01:00:10,800 --> 01:00:12,400
What kind of a man

870
01:00:14,400 --> 01:00:15,800
do you think

871
01:00:16,600 --> 01:00:18,360
a king should be?

872
01:00:19,440 --> 01:00:21,440
[tense music]

873
01:00:22,720 --> 01:00:25,880
Then what do you think, Lady Karaked?

874
01:00:28,000 --> 01:00:28,960
If I...

875
01:00:30,920 --> 01:00:33,800
ever got a chance to meet

876
01:00:34,880 --> 01:00:36,360
a king

877
01:00:36,840 --> 01:00:38,040
or two kings,

878
01:00:40,240 --> 01:00:41,560
I would tell them

879
01:00:43,240 --> 01:00:46,000
that kings should possess

880
01:00:47,840 --> 01:00:49,720
the Tenfold Virtue of the Ruler.

881
01:00:55,800 --> 01:00:57,800
[tense music]

882
01:01:01,440 --> 01:01:04,040
Do you have anything else to tell us?

883
01:01:05,080 --> 01:01:06,280
I do.

884
01:01:07,160 --> 01:01:08,240
I'm listening.

885
01:01:10,360 --> 01:01:14,040
Duke Wichayen is going to be defeated

886
01:01:15,520 --> 01:01:17,560
and punished for what he has done.

887
01:01:19,760 --> 01:01:22,120
But his wives and children
have nothing to do with it.

888
01:01:23,400 --> 01:01:24,840
I think...

889
01:01:27,160 --> 01:01:28,640
they should be spared.

890
01:01:30,440 --> 01:01:32,440
[heroic music]

891
01:01:37,200 --> 01:01:39,200
I'm getting jealous of you,

892
01:01:40,520 --> 01:01:41,640
Dech.

893
01:01:42,680 --> 01:01:43,600
[soft chuckle]

894
01:01:44,840 --> 01:01:47,520
Having a resourceful wife is enviable?

895
01:01:48,920 --> 01:01:50,480
I think it's actually sad.

896
01:01:51,480 --> 01:01:52,320
[Lord Pan chuckles]

897
01:01:54,160 --> 01:01:56,160
[heroic music]

898
01:02:03,600 --> 01:02:05,600
[heroic music continues]

899
01:02:10,160 --> 01:02:12,160
[tense music]

900
01:02:14,200 --> 01:02:15,560
Why can't I go in?

901
01:02:16,040 --> 01:02:17,120
Get out of my way!

902
01:02:17,480 --> 01:02:18,560
[Shorty] You servants!

903
01:02:18,960 --> 01:02:19,960
-How dare you.
-[thumping]

904
01:02:20,600 --> 01:02:21,840
-[whimpering]
-That's my father!

905
01:02:24,200 --> 01:02:25,160
[Shorty grunts]

906
01:02:25,760 --> 01:02:27,800
[tense music]

907
01:02:46,160 --> 01:02:48,160
[tense music continues]

908
01:02:58,880 --> 01:03:00,280
Resentful.

909
01:03:02,160 --> 01:03:04,360
No one is allowed to see the King.

910
01:03:05,320 --> 01:03:07,320
[tense music]

911
01:03:08,160 --> 01:03:10,480
Don't you know who I am?

912
01:03:10,960 --> 01:03:13,360
I am the Chancellor of Interior.

913
01:03:14,760 --> 01:03:17,160
I am the highest-ranking official.

914
01:03:18,440 --> 01:03:20,440
[tense music]

915
01:03:20,760 --> 01:03:21,840
[metal rasping]

916
01:03:25,320 --> 01:03:27,320
[tense music]

917
01:03:47,520 --> 01:03:49,520
[tense music continues]

918
01:03:56,840 --> 01:03:58,960
Give this to General Desfarges

919
01:03:59,640 --> 01:04:00,840
at the Bangkok fortress.

920
01:04:03,200 --> 01:04:04,600
I have an emergency situation

921
01:04:04,800 --> 01:04:06,960
that requires those soldiers in Lavo.

922
01:04:08,040 --> 01:04:09,400
[Phaulkon] It's time.

923
01:04:10,800 --> 01:04:11,760
Yes, my lord.

924
01:04:17,200 --> 01:04:19,200
[tense music]

925
01:04:19,640 --> 01:04:21,560
You sent word to General Desfarges

926
01:04:22,040 --> 01:04:24,240
to bring his men to Lavo.

927
01:04:27,120 --> 01:04:28,600
Are you planning a rebellion?

928
01:04:29,080 --> 01:04:32,200
Earl Phetracha and Count Sorasak
are planning to...

929
01:04:33,720 --> 01:04:34,760
against me.

930
01:04:36,520 --> 01:04:37,880
What choice do I have?

931
01:04:39,120 --> 01:04:40,640
If you hadn't started it,

932
01:04:41,360 --> 01:04:44,280
why would they want to kill you?

933
01:04:45,120 --> 01:04:46,320
[Mali] In this land,

934
01:04:46,440 --> 01:04:48,600
you've got food and shelter.

935
01:04:49,600 --> 01:04:51,680
Is that not enough?

936
01:04:56,840 --> 01:04:58,080
I have to do this.

937
01:04:58,760 --> 01:04:59,880
What about my life,

938
01:05:00,000 --> 01:05:02,240
your life and our children's lives?

939
01:05:03,440 --> 01:05:04,320
That's not true.

940
01:05:06,840 --> 01:05:08,440
You know full well

941
01:05:10,200 --> 01:05:11,600
who you are doing this for.

942
01:05:12,920 --> 01:05:14,720
[Mali] Don't use me and our children
as an excuse.

943
01:05:17,800 --> 01:05:21,320
France is not your homeland.

944
01:05:22,600 --> 01:05:25,040
But you are doing everything just for it.

945
01:05:26,880 --> 01:05:28,040
The truth is

946
01:05:28,600 --> 01:05:30,880
you are doing this for yourself,
aren't you?

947
01:05:31,080 --> 01:05:32,240
No, I'm not!

948
01:05:32,840 --> 01:05:34,520
[whimpers]
I can't take this anymore!

949
01:05:35,480 --> 01:05:36,480
Tong Guyomar.

950
01:05:36,560 --> 01:05:38,560
[tense music]

951
01:05:38,640 --> 01:05:40,640
[sobbing]
No.

952
01:05:42,440 --> 01:05:44,080
That's not true, Tong Guyomar.

953
01:05:48,160 --> 01:05:51,680
I can let you beat me up

954
01:05:52,040 --> 01:05:53,400
a hundred times...

955
01:05:56,280 --> 01:06:00,000
but I will never ever agree
with what you do.

956
01:06:03,400 --> 01:06:06,400
You will bring disgrace upon yourself,

957
01:06:07,560 --> 01:06:09,720
upon me,

958
01:06:09,960 --> 01:06:11,120
and upon our children.

959
01:06:12,480 --> 01:06:15,080
[Mali sobbing]

960
01:06:16,640 --> 01:06:18,040
At least,

961
01:06:19,400 --> 01:06:22,200
you should think of

962
01:06:22,800 --> 01:06:24,600
King Narai's kindness towards you.

963
01:06:25,280 --> 01:06:28,000
He thinks of you as a good friend.

964
01:06:29,480 --> 01:06:30,560
He trusts you.

965
01:06:31,840 --> 01:06:34,120
He likes everything about you.

966
01:06:35,960 --> 01:06:37,920
[whimpers]
And now,

967
01:06:38,800 --> 01:06:42,320
you are repaying his kindness

968
01:06:42,920 --> 01:06:44,240
by destroying his land.

969
01:06:46,120 --> 01:06:47,480
[Mali sobbing]

970
01:06:49,000 --> 01:06:51,000
[dramatic music]

971
01:07:17,240 --> 01:07:19,240
[dramatic music continues]

972
01:07:27,040 --> 01:07:29,600
[PHAULKON'S LETTER]

973
01:07:32,800 --> 01:07:34,800
[dramatic music]

974
01:07:48,160 --> 01:07:50,160
[light music]

975
01:08:02,480 --> 01:08:04,480
[light music continues]

976
01:08:20,480 --> 01:08:21,560
Karaked.

977
01:08:24,440 --> 01:08:25,440
Tomorrow,

978
01:08:26,360 --> 01:08:27,800
please stay with my mother.

979
01:08:30,040 --> 01:08:31,720
I have something to take care of.

980
01:08:40,360 --> 01:08:41,920
What is it?

981
01:08:42,640 --> 01:08:44,640
[tense music]

982
01:08:46,560 --> 01:08:47,480
[sighs]

983
01:08:55,520 --> 01:08:56,560
[soft chuckle]

984
01:08:56,880 --> 01:08:58,120
Don't worry about it.

985
01:08:59,440 --> 01:09:01,000
It's nothing serious.

986
01:09:03,080 --> 01:09:04,880
You avoid answering my question.

987
01:09:06,200 --> 01:09:08,320
Isn't it the same as lying?

988
01:09:10,280 --> 01:09:12,360
[groans]
Come on.

989
01:09:13,280 --> 01:09:15,400
Stay put here.

990
01:09:16,320 --> 01:09:18,480
[Dech] Don't let the servants out
of the house.

991
01:09:20,400 --> 01:09:22,320
I heard something bad

992
01:09:23,840 --> 01:09:25,440
about Duke Wichayen.

993
01:09:26,320 --> 01:09:27,760
Has he already done it?

994
01:09:29,000 --> 01:09:29,960
Yes.

995
01:09:31,680 --> 01:09:33,400
It's just like you said.

996
01:09:33,760 --> 01:09:35,760
[tense music]

997
01:09:36,160 --> 01:09:37,480
Duke Wichayen

998
01:09:38,640 --> 01:09:40,560
sent a messenger to Bangkok,

999
01:09:41,560 --> 01:09:44,680
asking for hundreds of soldiers
to come to Lavo.

1000
01:09:47,640 --> 01:09:49,120
And I also heard that

1001
01:09:49,960 --> 01:09:52,080
they are getting closer to Ayutthaya.

1002
01:09:54,080 --> 01:09:56,120
Are you going to stop them?

1003
01:09:57,040 --> 01:09:59,880
Lord Pan and I are going to do it.

1004
01:10:07,480 --> 01:10:09,480
[percussive music]

1005
01:10:16,480 --> 01:10:20,560
[speaking in French]
What brings you here?

1006
01:10:24,400 --> 01:10:27,160
[speaking in French]
We can't stay long but I want to warn you

1007
01:10:27,240 --> 01:10:30,400
about going to Lavo at this time.

1008
01:10:32,080 --> 01:10:34,240
What about it?

1009
01:10:35,080 --> 01:10:37,560
You know how unstable
the situation in Siam is right now.

1010
01:10:37,640 --> 01:10:40,200
it is in turmoil, especially in Lavo.

1011
01:10:40,360 --> 01:10:42,480
[Lord Pan] If you go there,

1012
01:10:42,560 --> 01:10:45,200
it might worsen the situation.

1013
01:10:45,480 --> 01:10:49,080
I've heard that thousands of people
are waiting to stop you on the way.

1014
01:10:49,360 --> 01:10:52,640
Even if you have deadly weapons,

1015
01:10:52,760 --> 01:10:56,360
you still can't defeat
thousands of people.

1016
01:10:56,920 --> 01:10:59,280
What are you talking about?
I'm just going there to help my people.

1017
01:10:59,520 --> 01:11:01,080
[speaking in French]
You mean Duke Wichayen?

1018
01:11:01,360 --> 01:11:03,720
You know that most Siam officials

1019
01:11:03,800 --> 01:11:05,840
despise him.

1020
01:11:05,920 --> 01:11:08,320
If you take
these fully-armed soldiers there,

1021
01:11:08,400 --> 01:11:10,680
people will take it the wrong way.

1022
01:11:11,680 --> 01:11:14,400
You make a good point.

1023
01:11:14,720 --> 01:11:18,360
You should take your men back to Bangkok.

1024
01:11:18,480 --> 01:11:22,960
You are their commander. You know that
this will lead them to their doom.

1025
01:11:23,120 --> 01:11:25,640
[Dech] You might not mind sacrificing
your life.

1026
01:11:25,720 --> 01:11:27,240
But sacrificing your men's lives

1027
01:11:27,320 --> 01:11:31,360
for nothing would be such a shame.

1028
01:11:31,840 --> 01:11:33,840
[tense music]

1029
01:11:50,440 --> 01:11:52,000
[Mali] <i><font color="white">People are saying all over the town</font></i>

1030
01:11:52,360 --> 01:11:54,760
that both of the heirs and Prince Pi

1031
01:11:55,320 --> 01:11:56,480
were all killed.

1032
01:11:57,680 --> 01:11:59,320
What are you going to do?

1033
01:12:03,200 --> 01:12:04,040
[sighs]

1034
01:12:04,200 --> 01:12:06,440
You still want those soldiers?

1035
01:12:07,440 --> 01:12:09,600
You still want the French troops

1036
01:12:09,720 --> 01:12:11,880
to destroy Lavo?

1037
01:12:15,000 --> 01:12:17,160
You want to kill everyone?

1038
01:12:20,280 --> 01:12:22,880
You know that you people can destroy

1039
01:12:25,280 --> 01:12:27,040
Lavo and Ayutthaya

1040
01:12:29,200 --> 01:12:30,960
just by firing your cannons.

1041
01:12:31,560 --> 01:12:33,560
[tense music]

1042
01:12:44,520 --> 01:12:45,840
My dear Tong Guyomar.

1043
01:12:49,760 --> 01:12:52,160
I've come too far to turn back now.

1044
01:12:54,400 --> 01:12:55,480
This matter

1045
01:12:56,440 --> 01:12:59,480
is not just about me
and General Desfarges.

1046
01:13:02,040 --> 01:13:04,160
[Phaulkon] It involves a lot of people,

1047
01:13:04,880 --> 01:13:06,360
the most important of which...

1048
01:13:08,080 --> 01:13:12,040
is Louis XIV of France.

1049
01:13:12,960 --> 01:13:14,960
[tense music]

1050
01:13:19,920 --> 01:13:21,080
[Ketsurang] <i><font color="white">Eventually,</font></i>

1051
01:13:21,160 --> 01:13:23,240
<i><font color="white">this upheaval will end.</font></i>

1052
01:13:23,840 --> 01:13:25,120
<i><font color="white">Many parts of history</font></i>

1053
01:13:25,480 --> 01:13:27,200
<i><font color="white">are disputed</font></i>

1054
01:13:27,680 --> 01:13:30,240
<i><font color="white">over their accuracy.</font></i>

1055
01:13:31,080 --> 01:13:33,240
<i><font color="white">But at the very least,
these following historical events</font></i>

1056
01:13:33,720 --> 01:13:35,960
<i><font color="white">during this time</font></i>

1057
01:13:36,440 --> 01:13:38,440
<i><font color="white">did actually happen.</font></i>

1058
01:13:40,520 --> 01:13:42,520
[percussive music]

1059
01:13:43,240 --> 01:13:44,320
[Ketsurang] <i><font color="white">Firstly,</font></i>

1060
01:13:44,440 --> 01:13:45,920
<i><font color="white">Prince Noi</font></i>

1061
01:13:46,040 --> 01:13:47,960
<i><font color="white">and Prince Apaiyatot</font></i>

1062
01:13:48,440 --> 01:13:50,000
<i><font color="white">were executed.</font></i>

1063
01:13:50,840 --> 01:13:51,960
<i><font color="white">Secondly,</font></i>

1064
01:13:52,080 --> 01:13:53,240
<i><font color="white">Prince Pi</font></i>

1065
01:13:53,360 --> 01:13:55,120
<i><font color="white">was also executed.</font></i>

1066
01:13:56,760 --> 01:13:57,840
<i><font color="white">Thirdly,</font></i>

1067
01:13:58,360 --> 01:14:00,120
<i><font color="white">though Earl Phetracha</font></i>

1068
01:14:00,920 --> 01:14:03,280
<i><font color="white">wasn't officially enthroned yet,</font></i>

1069
01:14:03,920 --> 01:14:06,560
<i><font color="white">he already acted as a king.</font></i>

1070
01:14:07,720 --> 01:14:11,160
<i><font color="white">He led monks and the common folk</font></i>

1071
01:14:11,280 --> 01:14:13,640
<i><font color="white">to invade the Royal Palace in Ayutthaya.</font></i>

1072
01:14:14,360 --> 01:14:16,520
<i><font color="white">He announced that he would
carry out the royal duties</font></i>

1073
01:14:17,280 --> 01:14:19,240
<i><font color="white">in place of King Narai.</font></i>

1074
01:14:20,960 --> 01:14:22,040
<i><font color="white">Fourthly,</font></i>

1075
01:14:22,280 --> 01:14:23,840
<i><font color="white">General Desfarges</font></i>

1076
01:14:24,320 --> 01:14:26,760
<i><font color="white">stopped sending the troops to Lavo</font></i>

1077
01:14:27,640 --> 01:14:30,160
<i><font color="white">because Lord Pan and Lord Dech</font></i>

1078
01:14:30,400 --> 01:14:32,040
<i><font color="white">managed to stopped him.</font></i>

1079
01:14:32,840 --> 01:14:34,680
<i><font color="white">But I suppose Duke Wichayen</font></i>

1080
01:14:35,040 --> 01:14:36,440
<i><font color="white">hasn't found out about it yet.</font></i>

1081
01:14:40,240 --> 01:14:41,840
[birds chirping]

1082
01:14:42,560 --> 01:14:44,560
[light music]

1083
01:14:46,840 --> 01:14:50,600
My lady. Back off.

1084
01:14:50,840 --> 01:14:52,480
Go away, Pin, Yaem.

1085
01:14:52,680 --> 01:14:54,480
My lady, be careful.

1086
01:14:55,360 --> 01:14:56,800
Hmm.

1087
01:14:58,680 --> 01:15:00,960
I think it might be twins.

1088
01:15:01,440 --> 01:15:03,360
[Prik] Your belly is quite big.

1089
01:15:04,360 --> 01:15:05,520
Sit down slowly.

1090
01:15:06,160 --> 01:15:07,120
Oh, oh, oh.

1091
01:15:07,320 --> 01:15:08,640
-Oh, right.
-Huh?

1092
01:15:11,280 --> 01:15:13,720
Twins run in my family.

1093
01:15:14,080 --> 01:15:14,920
[gasps]

1094
01:15:20,800 --> 01:15:21,960
Twins?

1095
01:15:23,640 --> 01:15:26,240
I might be carrying twins

1096
01:15:26,480 --> 01:15:27,960
because I also have a twin.

1097
01:15:28,320 --> 01:15:29,720
Considering my family's DNA

1098
01:15:29,840 --> 01:15:31,280
and genetic history,

1099
01:15:31,360 --> 01:15:34,080
there's a strong possibility
that I'm having twins.

1100
01:15:34,680 --> 01:15:36,800
-[Champa] Huh?
-[Dech chuckles softly]

1101
01:15:37,760 --> 01:15:39,760
What is a "DN" story?

1102
01:15:40,960 --> 01:15:41,800
[Champa groans]

1103
01:15:42,080 --> 01:15:43,960
What is kinetic?

1104
01:15:44,440 --> 01:15:47,600
You are saying odd things again.

1105
01:15:49,440 --> 01:15:50,960
I'm just saying that

1106
01:15:51,320 --> 01:15:54,480
I might be having twins.

1107
01:15:55,320 --> 01:15:56,280
[sighs]

1108
01:15:56,360 --> 01:15:58,360
[light music]

1109
01:15:58,840 --> 01:15:59,960
Give that to me.

1110
01:16:05,360 --> 01:16:06,680
What are you doing?

1111
01:16:07,920 --> 01:16:09,040
Sewing a pillow.

1112
01:16:09,600 --> 01:16:12,360
Oh, no! Stop it right now!

1113
01:16:13,480 --> 01:16:14,760
[Champa] Pin, Yaem.

1114
01:16:14,880 --> 01:16:15,960
-Prik.
-Yes, my lady.

1115
01:16:16,080 --> 01:16:17,280
Chuang, Chik.

1116
01:16:17,960 --> 01:16:21,200
Didn't you tell her that sewing
will cause the child to have a cleft lip?

1117
01:16:22,680 --> 01:16:24,400
[gasping]

1118
01:16:24,760 --> 01:16:26,760
[comical music]

1119
01:16:36,480 --> 01:16:39,040
Dech, I do agree with her.

1120
01:16:39,840 --> 01:16:43,520
She has such a big belly
for her first pregnancy.

1121
01:16:44,520 --> 01:16:47,960
If she's not carrying a giant child,
then it must be twins.

1122
01:16:48,680 --> 01:16:49,640
[soft chuckle]

1123
01:16:52,200 --> 01:16:53,480
That's great,

1124
01:16:53,600 --> 01:16:56,600
getting two babies in one pregnancy.

1125
01:16:58,160 --> 01:16:59,880
Please be twins.

1126
01:17:00,280 --> 01:17:01,720
[both chuckle]

1127
01:17:08,520 --> 01:17:10,280
I'm scared, <i><font color="white">Khun Pi</font></i>.

1128
01:17:12,720 --> 01:17:15,920
Giving birth in this era is somehow scary.

1129
01:17:16,360 --> 01:17:18,320
Oh, you don't have to be scared.

1130
01:17:18,440 --> 01:17:20,320
People here give birth all the time.

1131
01:17:20,400 --> 01:17:23,200
Besides, you eat the bananas

1132
01:17:23,280 --> 01:17:25,440
blessed by a notable monk every day.

1133
01:17:25,600 --> 01:17:27,600
You have nothing to worry about.

1134
01:17:27,800 --> 01:17:29,200
[chuckles]

1135
01:17:29,760 --> 01:17:30,640
Why?

1136
01:17:31,160 --> 01:17:32,320
My lord.

1137
01:17:33,080 --> 01:17:36,200
Why do you look so pale?

1138
01:17:36,600 --> 01:17:38,440
I think it must be very painful.

1139
01:17:38,800 --> 01:17:39,680
There you are.

1140
01:17:40,440 --> 01:17:41,680
[Dech sighs]

1141
01:17:42,800 --> 01:17:44,160
But you know what?

1142
01:17:46,040 --> 01:17:48,080
If I could feel the pain for you,

1143
01:17:49,920 --> 01:17:51,320
I would.

1144
01:17:52,120 --> 01:17:54,120
[romantic music]

1145
01:17:54,320 --> 01:17:55,520
Really?

1146
01:17:57,000 --> 01:17:58,040
Yes.

1147
01:17:59,800 --> 01:18:00,920
You're so sweet.

1148
01:18:03,400 --> 01:18:04,400
[clears throat]

1149
01:18:06,560 --> 01:18:08,600
[quirky music]

1150
01:18:08,680 --> 01:18:10,360
[both chuckle softly]

1151
01:18:14,960 --> 01:18:17,200
All right. I'll give it a try.

1152
01:18:17,680 --> 01:18:19,040
How much could it hurt?

1153
01:18:20,400 --> 01:18:23,200
It also hurt when I was
pregnant with you, Dech.

1154
01:18:24,440 --> 01:18:26,320
[Champa] But when you came out,

1155
01:18:26,440 --> 01:18:28,200
the pain just went away.

1156
01:18:29,000 --> 01:18:30,360
When that time comes,

1157
01:18:30,720 --> 01:18:32,360
you'll know it yourself.

1158
01:18:33,480 --> 01:18:34,680
Yes, Mother.

1159
01:18:38,080 --> 01:18:39,200
My lord.

1160
01:18:40,840 --> 01:18:42,800
Earl Phetracha sent you a message.

1161
01:18:43,080 --> 01:18:45,080
[tense music]

1162
01:18:59,200 --> 01:19:01,200
[tense music continues]

1163
01:19:11,520 --> 01:19:12,680
I have to go to Lavo

1164
01:19:12,920 --> 01:19:15,880
with Lord Pan and Rueang today.

1165
01:19:16,720 --> 01:19:18,160
What?

1166
01:19:18,640 --> 01:19:20,640
Can't you go there tomorrow?

1167
01:19:21,000 --> 01:19:22,160
I can't.

1168
01:19:22,720 --> 01:19:24,280
I have to go there as soon as possible.

1169
01:19:27,200 --> 01:19:29,000
Please take care of Karaked for me.

1170
01:19:32,480 --> 01:19:34,240
This time, I might be gone
for several days.

1171
01:19:35,000 --> 01:19:36,880
What is it about?

1172
01:19:37,800 --> 01:19:39,200
A state affair.

1173
01:19:46,480 --> 01:19:49,760
Please take care of Lady Mali
and her children.

1174
01:19:52,400 --> 01:19:54,400
[tense music]

1175
01:20:02,440 --> 01:20:03,640
My lord.

1176
01:20:05,280 --> 01:20:07,280
[action music]

1177
01:20:11,160 --> 01:20:12,520
Duke Wichayen.

1178
01:20:13,480 --> 01:20:15,440
King Narai wants to see you.

1179
01:20:17,520 --> 01:20:18,600
Really?

1180
01:20:18,960 --> 01:20:20,640
He is in serious condition.

1181
01:20:21,640 --> 01:20:23,400
That's why he's calling for you.

1182
01:20:24,640 --> 01:20:26,800
He is still alive?

1183
01:20:27,920 --> 01:20:28,960
Why

1184
01:20:29,520 --> 01:20:31,320
do you say such ominous things?

1185
01:20:32,080 --> 01:20:33,760
I didn't believe what people say,

1186
01:20:34,360 --> 01:20:35,720
-but--
-[Dech] You don't

1187
01:20:36,480 --> 01:20:38,240
trust us, do you?

1188
01:20:39,080 --> 01:20:41,080
[tense music]

1189
01:20:49,040 --> 01:20:51,040
[tense music continues]

1190
01:20:54,560 --> 01:20:56,040
I'm going now.

1191
01:20:56,880 --> 01:20:58,360
[Phaulkon] I trust both of you...

1192
01:20:59,840 --> 01:21:01,840
without any doubt.

1193
01:21:04,840 --> 01:21:06,160
Get the litter ready.

1194
01:21:06,400 --> 01:21:07,520
Yes, my lord.

1195
01:21:10,680 --> 01:21:12,680
[tense music]

1196
01:21:22,680 --> 01:21:24,600
[Phaulkon] Has the King recovered?

1197
01:21:25,080 --> 01:21:26,840
