before I die?

1344
01:32:55,520 --> 01:32:56,400
Yes.

1345
01:32:59,280 --> 01:33:01,280
[somber music]

1346
01:33:14,280 --> 01:33:16,200
Have you ever loved me?

1347
01:33:25,120 --> 01:33:26,360
Did you ever

1348
01:33:28,080 --> 01:33:30,160
have me in your heart?

1349
01:33:33,680 --> 01:33:36,480
[whimpers]

1350
01:33:47,760 --> 01:33:49,760
[dramatic music]

1351
01:33:56,320 --> 01:33:58,560
[sobbing]

1352
01:33:59,880 --> 01:34:00,920
Phaulkon.

1353
01:34:05,640 --> 01:34:07,080
I promise you

1354
01:34:10,040 --> 01:34:11,480
that you will be

1355
01:34:13,120 --> 01:34:15,520
my only husband

1356
01:34:17,080 --> 01:34:18,640
for as long as I live.

1357
01:34:19,600 --> 01:34:21,600
[dramatic music]

1358
01:34:33,160 --> 01:34:34,280
Tong Guyomar.

1359
01:34:38,800 --> 01:34:40,600
[whimpers]

1360
01:34:46,440 --> 01:34:47,560
Let's go.

1361
01:34:48,120 --> 01:34:50,120
[whimpers]

1362
01:34:56,200 --> 01:34:58,200
[somber music]

1363
01:35:20,800 --> 01:35:22,800
[somber music continues]

1364
01:35:31,240 --> 01:35:33,360
[Mali] <i><font color="white">I'm sorry, Constance.</font></i>

1365
01:35:36,040 --> 01:35:38,520
<i><font color="white">Even if you die today,</font></i>

1366
01:35:41,640 --> 01:35:43,880
<i><font color="white">I still can't love you.</font></i>

1367
01:35:45,240 --> 01:35:47,240
[somber music]

1368
01:35:53,160 --> 01:35:54,560
[Ketsurang] <i><font color="white">Duke Wichayen</font></i>

1369
01:35:54,800 --> 01:35:57,040
<i><font color="white">died on the 5th of June.</font></i>

1370
01:35:58,280 --> 01:36:01,200
<i><font color="white">Two days after he died,</font></i>

1371
01:36:01,920 --> 01:36:03,920
<i><font color="white">Prince Pi was executed.</font></i>

1372
01:36:05,800 --> 01:36:08,240
<i><font color="white">King Narai passed away</font></i>

1373
01:36:08,720 --> 01:36:10,920
<i><font color="white">on July 17th,</font></i>

1374
01:36:11,040 --> 01:36:12,960
<i><font color="white">in the year 1688.</font></i>

1375
01:36:13,800 --> 01:36:16,600
<i><font color="white">Count Sorasak didn't want
to be the new king.</font></i>

1376
01:36:18,240 --> 01:36:20,080
<i><font color="white">So, Earl Phetracha</font></i>

1377
01:36:20,360 --> 01:36:22,200
<i><font color="white">was enthroned</font></i>

1378
01:36:22,320 --> 01:36:24,080
<i><font color="white">as the first king </font></i>

1379
01:36:24,560 --> 01:36:27,040
<i><font color="white">of the Ban Phlu Luang Dynasty.</font></i>

1380
01:36:28,200 --> 01:36:30,680
<i><font color="white">He appointed Count Sorasak</font></i>

1381
01:36:31,400 --> 01:36:35,840
<i><font color="white">as the Viceroy living at the Front Palace.</font></i>

1382
01:36:37,360 --> 01:36:40,520
<i><font color="white">The new King</font></i>

1383
01:36:40,760 --> 01:36:42,440
<i><font color="white">promoted Lord Pan</font></i>

1384
01:36:43,040 --> 01:36:45,840
<i><font color="white">to Duke Kosathibodi,</font></i>

1385
01:36:46,560 --> 01:36:48,040
<i><font color="white">Minister of the Treasury</font></i>

1386
01:36:49,320 --> 01:36:50,800
<i><font color="white">and promoted Lord Rueang</font></i>

1387
01:36:50,960 --> 01:36:52,560
<i><font color="white">to Earl Ramnarong.</font></i>

1388
01:36:53,800 --> 01:36:55,080
Khun Pi <i><font color="white">Dech</font></i>

1389
01:36:55,480 --> 01:36:56,680
<i><font color="white">was promoted to</font></i>

1390
01:36:57,040 --> 01:36:59,720
<i><font color="white">Marquess Wisut Sakorn.</font></i>

1391
01:37:01,160 --> 01:37:02,520
And I,

1392
01:37:02,640 --> 01:37:03,920
Ketsurang,

1393
01:37:04,160 --> 01:37:05,840
was promoted to

1394
01:37:06,080 --> 01:37:08,480
Marchioness Wisut Sakorn.

1395
01:37:09,160 --> 01:37:13,200
[giggles]

1396
01:37:14,080 --> 01:37:14,920
Ow.

1397
01:37:16,240 --> 01:37:17,240
Ow!

1398
01:37:18,280 --> 01:37:20,280
[Karaked groaning]

1399
01:37:21,040 --> 01:37:22,520
[heavy breathing]

1400
01:37:22,640 --> 01:37:25,120
-It hurts!
-[woman 3] Push, my lady.

1401
01:37:25,520 --> 01:37:28,280
-[Karaked screaming]
-Push, my lady.

1402
01:37:28,360 --> 01:37:30,800
-Push, my lady.
-My lady.

1403
01:37:30,920 --> 01:37:33,320
Hang in there, my lady.

1404
01:37:33,440 --> 01:37:35,200
Push, my lady.

1405
01:37:35,280 --> 01:37:36,440
[both screaming]

1406
01:37:36,560 --> 01:37:37,520
Push!

1407
01:37:37,680 --> 01:37:39,760
[both screaming]

1408
01:37:39,920 --> 01:37:42,920
Hey, you!

1409
01:37:43,040 --> 01:37:46,760
Hey, hours have passed.
Why hasn't the baby come out?

1410
01:37:46,840 --> 01:37:48,840
[playful music]

1411
01:37:52,760 --> 01:37:54,040
Push some more.

1412
01:37:54,320 --> 01:37:56,760
[both screaming]

1413
01:37:57,400 --> 01:38:01,240
Just cut me open.
I can't take this anymore. Do it!

1414
01:38:01,360 --> 01:38:02,480
-My lady.
-Cut me open!

1415
01:38:02,600 --> 01:38:04,880
Hey, I'm losing my patience, bitch!

1416
01:38:05,000 --> 01:38:05,840
Prik.

1417
01:38:07,160 --> 01:38:08,400
Yes, my lady.

1418
01:38:08,960 --> 01:38:10,120
-Push, my lady.
-[screaming]

1419
01:38:10,240 --> 01:38:13,240
-Push!
-[screaming]

1420
01:38:13,400 --> 01:38:15,720
[baby crying]

1421
01:38:15,840 --> 01:38:18,320
[Pin] The baby came out!

1422
01:38:18,560 --> 01:38:20,520
It's a boy.

1423
01:38:20,680 --> 01:38:21,760
I have a son?

1424
01:38:22,280 --> 01:38:26,960
-[baby crying]
-[Karaked screaming]

1425
01:38:28,320 --> 01:38:29,800
-Another one came out!
-[Prik] What?

1426
01:38:30,040 --> 01:38:31,520
She has twins!

1427
01:38:31,600 --> 01:38:34,080
-[all screaming]
-Wait, Yaem!

1428
01:38:34,440 --> 01:38:35,520
What did you just say?

1429
01:38:35,760 --> 01:38:37,160
Dech.

1430
01:38:38,040 --> 01:38:40,080
You had twins just as we expected.

1431
01:38:40,320 --> 01:38:42,000
You don't have to get too excited.

1432
01:38:44,360 --> 01:38:46,360
[light music]

1433
01:38:59,160 --> 01:39:01,080
[baby crying]

1434
01:39:06,120 --> 01:39:08,120
[quirky music]

1435
01:39:13,960 --> 01:39:15,920
I feel so gross.

1436
01:39:17,040 --> 01:39:17,920
It's hot

1437
01:39:18,680 --> 01:39:19,560
and smelly.

1438
01:39:19,640 --> 01:39:21,800
[groans]
My head is itchy.

1439
01:39:23,080 --> 01:39:25,800
[groaning]

1440
01:39:27,000 --> 01:39:28,640
[Pin] Please take your medicine.

1441
01:39:29,680 --> 01:39:31,680
[quirky music]

1442
01:39:34,000 --> 01:39:34,880
[coughs]

1443
01:39:35,880 --> 01:39:37,480
[groans]

1444
01:39:42,520 --> 01:39:44,520
[dreamy music]

1445
01:39:44,840 --> 01:39:48,640
[cooing]

1446
01:39:49,120 --> 01:39:50,320
[Karaked] What is it?

1447
01:39:50,640 --> 01:39:51,520
[soft chuckle]

1448
01:39:51,640 --> 01:39:53,360
They are ten days old, right?

1449
01:39:54,160 --> 01:39:55,720
Actually, they are 12 days old.

1450
01:39:55,840 --> 01:39:57,520
Oh, really?
[soft chuckle]

1451
01:39:58,560 --> 01:40:00,440
They look so adorable.

1452
01:40:01,440 --> 01:40:03,320
What are their names, Karaked?

1453
01:40:04,360 --> 01:40:06,480
Rueang and Rit.

1454
01:40:06,960 --> 01:40:09,120
Oh, Rueang and Rit.

1455
01:40:09,600 --> 01:40:10,520
All right.

1456
01:40:15,560 --> 01:40:16,640
[sighs]

1457
01:40:17,040 --> 01:40:20,400
I've never seen anyone coming up
with their child's name within a day.

1458
01:40:20,480 --> 01:40:21,600
[sighs deeply]

1459
01:40:21,840 --> 01:40:23,320
People don't do that.

1460
01:40:23,960 --> 01:40:25,320
[Champa] At the earliest, they do that

1461
01:40:25,560 --> 01:40:27,320
on the day the baby's
first month is celebrated.

1462
01:40:27,800 --> 01:40:29,080
It's fine.

1463
01:40:29,520 --> 01:40:32,920
She'll name them Rueang and Rit

1464
01:40:33,040 --> 01:40:34,160
no matter when it is.

1465
01:40:36,120 --> 01:40:37,760
I'm so tired of you, Prik.

1466
01:40:39,000 --> 01:40:40,040
Look at you.

1467
01:40:40,320 --> 01:40:42,120
You've completely changed
like a different person.

1468
01:40:42,680 --> 01:40:43,880
Yes, my lady.

1469
01:40:44,120 --> 01:40:46,320
Anyway, I'm not a thief.

1470
01:40:53,480 --> 01:40:54,640
Lord Pan,

1471
01:40:55,120 --> 01:40:57,000
please make yourself at home.

1472
01:40:57,240 --> 01:40:58,400
Thank you.

1473
01:40:59,320 --> 01:41:01,560
You two, bring those things and follow me.

1474
01:41:01,680 --> 01:41:02,840
[both] Yes, my lady.

1475
01:41:05,400 --> 01:41:06,560
[Lord Pan] Ahh.

1476
01:41:06,640 --> 01:41:08,040
Lord Pan.

1477
01:41:08,200 --> 01:41:10,480
-Yes?
-How is Lady Mali doing?

1478
01:41:11,400 --> 01:41:12,600
Hmm.

1479
01:41:12,760 --> 01:41:14,080
She has been released from prison.

1480
01:41:15,600 --> 01:41:17,080
King Phetracha

1481
01:41:17,800 --> 01:41:19,320
put her in the royal kitchen

1482
01:41:20,320 --> 01:41:21,960
because she's good at making desserts.

1483
01:41:22,680 --> 01:41:23,960
That's good.

1484
01:41:24,200 --> 01:41:25,920
I'm so worried about her.

1485
01:41:27,000 --> 01:41:28,280
The Viceroy

1486
01:41:29,400 --> 01:41:30,600
asked her to be his concubine

1487
01:41:31,560 --> 01:41:32,840
but she refused.

1488
01:41:34,160 --> 01:41:35,440
She is strong-willed.

1489
01:41:37,480 --> 01:41:39,160
That's the right thing for her to do.

1490
01:41:40,440 --> 01:41:42,440
[tranquil music]

1491
01:41:48,680 --> 01:41:51,160
-Excuse me.
-[Lord Pan] Wait.

1492
01:41:53,280 --> 01:41:55,040
[Lord Pan] Can you answer a question?

1493
01:41:55,920 --> 01:41:57,080
You know

1494
01:41:57,480 --> 01:41:59,480
what I'm going to ask.

1495
01:41:59,760 --> 01:42:01,240
How did you know about that matter?

1496
01:42:01,680 --> 01:42:03,680
[tense music]

1497
01:42:04,160 --> 01:42:05,600
You have to answer that.

1498
01:42:07,520 --> 01:42:09,920
I will, but...

1499
01:42:10,160 --> 01:42:13,480
I'm just thinking
because it's hard to explain.

1500
01:42:15,280 --> 01:42:17,040
[Dech] Even if it's hard,
you still have to answer.

1501
01:42:18,360 --> 01:42:19,920
I know.

1502
01:42:22,960 --> 01:42:23,800
[sighs]

1503
01:42:25,960 --> 01:42:27,320
It's because

1504
01:42:28,120 --> 01:42:31,520
the era where I was actually born in
before I came here

1505
01:42:32,560 --> 01:42:34,560
is an era in the future.

1506
01:42:34,640 --> 01:42:36,640
[tense music]

1507
01:42:36,720 --> 01:42:37,600
What?

1508
01:42:40,600 --> 01:42:42,040
Are you saying that

1509
01:42:43,480 --> 01:42:45,800
you were born in the future

1510
01:42:46,520 --> 01:42:48,360
and then went back in time

1511
01:42:48,880 --> 01:42:50,760
to be reborn in the past?

1512
01:42:51,640 --> 01:42:52,640
Yes.

1513
01:42:53,600 --> 01:42:54,920
I was reborn here.

1514
01:42:55,560 --> 01:42:56,640
I'm going to believe you

1515
01:42:57,560 --> 01:42:59,160
without any doubt.

1516
01:43:01,280 --> 01:43:02,600
But I have to ask.

1517
01:43:03,320 --> 01:43:05,400
Do people in the future

1518
01:43:06,320 --> 01:43:09,640
know all the things
that happened in this era?

1519
01:43:10,480 --> 01:43:12,680
Yes, they know everything.

1520
01:43:14,760 --> 01:43:15,800
[Dech] Everything?

1521
01:43:16,560 --> 01:43:17,800
Who told them?

1522
01:43:18,360 --> 01:43:20,480
[giggles]

1523
01:43:20,560 --> 01:43:22,720
Why are you laughing?

1524
01:43:23,600 --> 01:43:24,960
[sighs]

1525
01:43:25,960 --> 01:43:27,360
Who told them?

1526
01:43:29,080 --> 01:43:31,960
There are things called chronicles,

1527
01:43:32,200 --> 01:43:33,480
research,

1528
01:43:33,960 --> 01:43:35,240
analyses,

1529
01:43:35,680 --> 01:43:36,880
testimonies,

1530
01:43:37,400 --> 01:43:40,920
and written records that were passed down.

1531
01:43:42,560 --> 01:43:44,120
Is that what you call

1532
01:43:44,240 --> 01:43:46,360
his...

1533
01:43:47,080 --> 01:43:49,160
"history", right?

1534
01:43:49,640 --> 01:43:51,960
Yes, that's right.

1535
01:43:52,200 --> 01:43:54,200
So, you know...

1536
01:43:55,000 --> 01:43:56,640
the history of everyone?

1537
01:43:57,400 --> 01:43:58,720
Not everyone.

1538
01:43:58,960 --> 01:44:01,680
Just the important ones,

1539
01:44:02,480 --> 01:44:05,800
like Lord Lek and Lord Pan.

1540
01:44:06,360 --> 01:44:09,840
You two are well-known in my era.

1541
01:44:09,960 --> 01:44:12,880
People call you "Kosa Lek" and "Kosa Pan."

1542
01:44:14,880 --> 01:44:16,880
[light music]

1543
01:44:19,720 --> 01:44:22,040
[giggles]
You?

1544
01:44:22,840 --> 01:44:24,480
There are records of you too,

1545
01:44:24,600 --> 01:44:27,520
because you were the third minister
in Lord Pan's mission.

1546
01:44:30,920 --> 01:44:33,200
What about my father?

1547
01:44:33,560 --> 01:44:35,640
What does history say about him?

1548
01:44:35,880 --> 01:44:38,360
That he was the one
who wrote the book, Jindamanee.

1549
01:44:40,000 --> 01:44:43,320
They still use that book in your era?

1550
01:44:43,560 --> 01:44:44,880
Not anymore.

1551
01:44:45,120 --> 01:44:48,640
There are new ones but they are
written based on Jindamanee

1552
01:44:48,880 --> 01:44:51,040
with added alphabets

1553
01:44:51,160 --> 01:44:54,120
from 37 to 44.

1554
01:44:55,320 --> 01:44:56,600
Hmm.

1555
01:44:57,280 --> 01:45:00,560
And how did you get here?

1556
01:45:02,000 --> 01:45:03,720
Lord Pan.

1557
01:45:04,080 --> 01:45:05,840
You said you wouldn't ask about that.

1558
01:45:06,320 --> 01:45:08,680
Oh, that's true.

1559
01:45:09,200 --> 01:45:10,960
And I don't even know how to answer that.

1560
01:45:11,040 --> 01:45:11,880
[giggles]

1561
01:45:11,960 --> 01:45:13,960
[quirky music]

1562
01:45:14,240 --> 01:45:15,840
[Dech] How many years have passed
since then?

1563
01:45:15,920 --> 01:45:16,800
Yes.

1564
01:45:17,040 --> 01:45:19,120
Between our era and your era.

1565
01:45:21,000 --> 01:45:22,960
You want the exact number?

1566
01:45:25,080 --> 01:45:27,080
It's actually 329 years.

1567
01:45:28,120 --> 01:45:30,240
[both] Did you say 329 years?

1568
01:45:31,480 --> 01:45:33,480
[light music]

1569
01:45:39,040 --> 01:45:40,320
[man 2] Don't lose.

1570
01:45:42,960 --> 01:45:44,120
Let's start if you're ready.

1571
01:45:45,160 --> 01:45:47,160
[quirky music]

1572
01:45:50,360 --> 01:45:53,800
-[rustling]
-[men shouting]

1573
01:45:55,760 --> 01:45:57,760
[playful music]

1574
01:46:10,640 --> 01:46:12,640
[playful music continues]

1575
01:46:23,640 --> 01:46:27,600
-[rustling]
-[men shouting]

1576
01:46:28,520 --> 01:46:34,240
[all shouting]

1577
01:46:38,560 --> 01:46:40,040
Lady Mali.

1578
01:46:40,640 --> 01:46:42,440
Can I have some desserts?

1579
01:46:43,000 --> 01:46:45,520
You can have some if you can
call them by the right names.

1580
01:46:46,960 --> 01:46:48,960
[uplifting music]

1581
01:46:50,160 --> 01:46:51,480
[Mali] What is this called?

1582
01:46:51,880 --> 01:46:53,120
It's <i><font color="white">thong yip.</font></i>

1583
01:46:54,640 --> 01:46:55,760
[Mali] What about this, Kaew?

1584
01:46:56,120 --> 01:46:58,520
It's <i><font color="white">foi thong,</font></i> isn't it?

1585
01:46:59,000 --> 01:47:00,440
That's correct.

1586
01:47:02,120 --> 01:47:03,800
-[Mali] What about this?
-[Kaew] It's <i><font color="white">thong yot.</font></i>

1587
01:47:03,880 --> 01:47:06,440
[Mali] Good job, you two.

1588
01:47:09,720 --> 01:47:10,920
Try it.

1589
01:47:13,120 --> 01:47:15,120
[uplifting music]

1590
01:47:23,240 --> 01:47:24,400
Your mother

1591
01:47:25,080 --> 01:47:27,120
wanted you to marry Lady Chanwad.

1592
01:47:28,640 --> 01:47:30,840
[Lord Rueang] And I adored Karaked.

1593
01:47:32,160 --> 01:47:33,960
If things have gone
according to her plans,

1594
01:47:34,480 --> 01:47:36,040
my wife would be yours

1595
01:47:36,840 --> 01:47:38,440
and your wife would be mine.

1596
01:47:38,840 --> 01:47:40,360
[chuckles]

1597
01:47:42,480 --> 01:47:43,320
[clears throat]

1598
01:47:43,400 --> 01:47:45,400
[comical music]

1599
01:47:45,760 --> 01:47:47,200
Forget what I just said.

1600
01:47:49,040 --> 01:47:49,880
[sighs]

1601
01:47:49,960 --> 01:47:51,960
[comical music]

1602
01:47:53,440 --> 01:47:55,560
I completely adore my wife.

1603
01:47:56,080 --> 01:47:58,080
[light music]

1604
01:48:01,360 --> 01:48:02,800
You should, Dech.

1605
01:48:05,840 --> 01:48:07,120
[Lord Rueang] Lady Karaked

1606
